HEADWORD: Kirmess
<hw>Kir"mess</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[D.
<ets>kermis</ets>; cf. G. <ets>kirmes</ets>; prop., church mass. See
<er>Church</er>, and <er>Mass</er> a religious service.]</ety> <def>In
Europe, particularly in Belgium and Holland, and outdoor festival and
fair; in the United States, generally an indoor entertainment and fair
combined.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

